-------------------------
initial git on folder

git init
-------------------------
add all files in this folder to git:

git add .
-------------------------
commit these new files
and put message on this change

git commit -m "first commit"(m stand for message)
-------------------------
add the repository address to git:
origin is convention name for address of repository:

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/project.git
means after this named https://github.com/username/project.git as origin
we can named it sina!
--------------------------
see results:

git remote:
return origin (the address of repository)
git remote -v
return address with details (v stand for verbose)
--------------------------
git branch -M main
means named this branch to main
mabe its main already, so nothing changed
but mabe its named as master, its make it to main
if there is another branch named main
this command force this branch to replace it
(before: branch name = master
command: git branch -M main
after:  branch name = main)

git branch -m main
do same thing
but if there is other branch named main
it dos not force it to replace
we got error in this situation
-----------------------------
git push -u origin main

-u stand for upstream-set
Link my local branch main to the remote branch origin/main and make it the default.
after this can simply write "git push"
instead of "git push origin main" (push current branch to main branch in origin(remote))